BONGANI Ngobeni’s home was almost burnt down after the 30-year-old from Nkambako Village in Limpopo travelled home from Joburg the day before lockdown after testing positive. READ: COMEDIAN TREVOR NOAH RECEIVES DEATH THREATS He told Daily Sun yesterday he was accused on social media of travelling in a taxi.“It’s a lie. I took a bakkie to Dzumeri Village and hitchhiked to my village.” Bongani said he stayed away from people and the next day, officials took him to Letaba Hospital. Limpopo health’s Neil Shikwambana said Bongani was first taken into isolation in the province.